cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.AI 

This paper discusses the challenges and opportunities of deploying fog computing for intelligent IoT applications, specifically in the context of connected and autonomous vehicles. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Additionally, the paper also discusses the use of advanced technologies such as 5G New Radio, which falls under cs.IT (Information Theory). The concept of fog computing itself falls under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper also discusses the use of AI in the context of autonomous vehicles, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
